like the plague.

135
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,323
Makes it difficult to see Jeff.

136
00:06:05,489 --> 00:06:08,727
Maybe there's something I could do.

137
00:06:08,852 --> 00:06:10,578
You know, maybe I could
apologize to her.

138
00:06:10,744 --> 00:06:12,622
Do you have something
to apologize for?

139
00:06:12,788 --> 00:06:15,041
I never told you what happened?

140
00:06:15,207 --> 00:06:16,702
No.

141
00:06:16,827 --> 00:06:18,586
Do you want to talk about it?

142
00:06:18,752 --> 00:06:20,006
Nah.

143
00:06:20,131 --> 00:06:22,007
Let me just leave
the past in the past.

144
00:06:24,216 --> 00:06:25,878
Hey, I've been meaning to ask you.

145
00:06:26,003 --> 00:06:29,389
Do you think something's off
with Juliet?

146
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:31,583
She's been so... quiet.

147
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:32,601
I don't know.

148
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,686
Less... combative.

149
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:36,646
Isn't that a good thing?

150
00:06:36,812 --> 00:06:39,725
Yeah, I'm sure it is.

151
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:41,377
She had a tough year.

152
00:06:41,502 --> 00:06:43,987
It'll be good for her...
New year, back to school.

153
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:48,407
(Sighs)
I'm so tired.

154
00:06:59,569 --> 00:07:02,281
