264
00:11:56,381 --> 00:11:58,127
on you earlier.

265
00:11:58,252 --> 00:12:00,470
Everything okay?

266
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:03,081
Yeah. I just have to take care
of one thing.

267
00:12:03,206 --> 00:12:05,184
Tyler, I know you don't trust me,

268
00:12:05,309 --> 00:12:06,885
but I'm trying to get back.

269
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:08,603
Well, it's a little hard to trust you

270
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:11,731
when you were using me
to get back at your husband.

271
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:15,477
So this thing
that you have to take care of...

272
00:12:15,602 --> 00:12:17,946
Does it involve Andrew?

273
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,031
Have you seen him?

274
00:12:20,197 --> 00:12:24,269
I don't want him
to know that I'm here.

275
00:12:24,394 --> 00:12:25,821
Look, Martin/Charles just released

276
00:12:25,946 --> 00:12:27,105
their year-end statements.

277
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:29,415
I'm just trying
to get my hands on a copy.

278
00:12:29,581 --> 00:12:30,876
Tell me why.

279
00:12:31,001 --> 00:12:33,920
You know, since we're
trusting each other.

280
00:12:34,461 --> 00:12:37,249
Am I talking to Tyler Barrett,
loyal employee,

281
00:12:37,374 --> 00:12:39,885
or Tyler Barrett...

282
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:41,761
The father of my baby?

283
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,139
How about a guy who's got

284
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:45,424
a high-level job at Martin/Charles?

285
00:12:45,549 --> 00:12:47,309
If Andrew's doing something illegal,

286
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:49,894
I'd like to get out
before you expose him.

287
00:12:51,754 --> 00:12:53,298
Okay.

288
00:12:53,423 --> 00:12:55,601
Look, I believe that Andrew issues

289
00:12:55,726 --> 00:12:57,281
one set of statements
to his investors,

290
00:12:57,406 --> 00:12:59,195
but I think he keeps
the real ones hidden.

291
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:01,948
Uh, I want to get my hands
on one so I have some proof,

292
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:04,367
but his office security
is just too tight.

293
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,279
Can you get into your apartment

294
00:13:07,404 --> 00:13:08,831
without Andrew knowing
you were there?

295
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:10,582
Uh, I would imagine so.

296
00:13:10,707 --> 00:13:12,167
Why?

297
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:14,036
Because home security tends to be

298
00:13:14,161 --> 00:13:15,537
more lax than office security,

299
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:18,047
even though we have information
in both places.

300
00:13:18,485 --> 00:13:21,460
If you want to hack Andrew,
home is the place.

301
00:13:21,585 --> 00:13:23,719
Thank you.

302
00:13:23,885 --> 00:13:26,632
Oh, uh, Tyler, I-I have to run.

303
00:13:26,757 --> 00:13:28,683
I-I... I will call you.

304
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:31,520
(Door bell jingling)

305
00:13:31,645 --> 00:13:32,854
Henry!

306
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:39,652
God, it's so good to see you.

307
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:42,864
What are you... what are you
doing here, Siobhan?

308
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,973
Well, I... I know you always
come this way

309
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:48,871
after you drop the boys at
school, and I needed to see you.

310
00:13:48,996 --> 00:13:50,872
I miss you.

311
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:53,158
You know who I miss?

312
00:13:53,283 --> 00:13:54,667
My wife.

313
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,797
You brought Bridget Kelly
into our lives.

314
00:13:58,922 --> 00:14:01,048
But if it wasn't for you...

315
00:14:01,542 --> 00:14:03,676
Gemma would be here today.

316
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:06,095
Wait. Please don't go.

317
00:14:06,261 --> 00:14:08,181
Henry, I can explain this.

318
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,682
Sit down with me.

319
00:14:11,308 --> 00:14:13,436
I-I can explain everything.
I swear.

320
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,120
{pub}You have something
you want to say to me...

321
00:14:21,245 --> 00:14:22,195
You say it right now.

322
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:24,540
I-I can't right on the street.

323
00:14:24,665 --> 00:14:26,741
I mean, just...
Give me five minutes.

324
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:27,827
Please, I'll explain everything.

325
00:14:27,952 --> 00:14:28,993
I'm busy.

326
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:30,763
I'm swamped with publisher meetings.

327
00:14:30,888 --> 00:14:32,181
For your book?

328
00:14:32,306 --> 00:14:33,800
Henry, that's great.

329
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:36,250
Since when do you care about my book?

330
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:39,355
No matter what happened,

331
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,441
I think you're an amazing writer.

332
00:14:41,566 --> 00:14:42,840
You know that.

333
00:14:44,784 --> 00:14:46,846
Save it, Siobhan.

334
00:14:46,971 --> 00:14:48,180
I'm late.

335
00:14:48,305 --> 00:14:49,472
Taxi!

336
00:15:02,085 --> 00:15:03,903
Siobhan, are you okay?

337
00:15:07,374 --> 00:15:09,168
Yeah.

338
00:15:09,293 --> 00:15:12,370
It's just been a rough couple days.

339
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:13,756
(Sighs)

340
00:15:13,881 --> 00:15:15,374
Uh, you know what?

341
00:15:15,499 --> 00:15:17,510
Maybe I can, uh... I don't know,

342
00:15:17,635 --> 00:15:19,011
maybe I can move some stuff around.

343
00:15:19,136 --> 00:15:20,503
You want to meet on Friday?

344
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:22,298
10:00 a.M.?

345
00:15:22,423 --> 00:15:24,350
Okay.

346
00:15:24,475 --> 00:15:26,425
Usual place?

347
00:15:27,611 --> 00:15:29,971
No, we don't have
a usual place anymore.

348
00:15:31,815 --> 00:15:33,140
How about the loft?

349
00:15:33,306 --> 00:15:35,651
I'll see you there.

350
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:47,072
Bridget Kelly's a ghost.

351
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:49,323
I... I can't even prove
that she was in New York

352
00:15:49,489 --> 00:15:50,700
when Gemma Butler was murdered.

353
00:15:50,866 --> 00:15:53,463
Forensics on the gun
seem pretty conclusive.

354
00:15:53,588 --> 00:15:56,789
Charlie Young, aka John Delario,
was the shooter.

355
00:15:56,955 --> 00:15:58,100
Yeah, I don't doubt
he killed Gemma Butler.

356
00:15:58,225 --> 00:15:59,500
I doubt he killed himself.

357
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:01,586
You think someone staged the scene?

358
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:03,139
Angle of the gun was off.

359
00:16:03,264 --> 00:16:05,590
And Delario's hands tested
positive for powder residue,

360
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:06,809
but trace amounts.

361
00:16:06,934 --> 00:16:09,111
Which point to him having fired
the gun hours before,

362
00:16:09,236 --> 00:16:11,178
and yet he died instantaneously.

363
00:16:11,344 --> 00:16:13,149
NYPD seem to believe otherwise.

364
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:14,817
Yeah, because Delario
is one of their own.

365
00:16:14,942 --> 00:16:16,786
They want this whole thing
to go away quickly.

366
00:16:16,911 --> 00:16:19,312
And bringing Bridget Kelly
into it only complicates things.

367
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:21,814
Why would Kelly kill Delario?

368
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:23,793
Hell if I know.
I... (Chuckles)

369
00:16:23,918 --> 00:16:26,078
The Bridget Kelly I knew in Wyoming

370
00:16:26,203 --> 00:16:27,945
was not a kidnapper or a killer.

371
00:16:28,955 --> 00:16:30,239
Okay, let's just focus

372
00:16:30,405 --> 00:16:31,501
on what's in front of us.

373
00:16:31,626 --> 00:16:33,135
Let's try to figure out how and why

374
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:34,670
Bridget and Charlie became a team.

375
00:16:34,795 --> 00:16:37,056
I mean, seriously,
how does a stripper from Wyoming

376
00:16:37,181 --> 00:16:39,425
hook up with a retired cop
from Brooklyn?

377
00:16:39,706 --> 00:16:42,001
Did a little digging into your guy.

378
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:44,847
Traffic cam shows him
blowing through a red light

379
00:16:44,972 --> 00:16:47,632
on September 8,
driving down Montauk highway.

380
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:49,018
John Delario was driving

381
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:51,844
on the main road into the
Hamptons, September 8?

382
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:54,096
The same weekend
Bridget Kelly was there.

383
00:16:54,262 --> 00:16:55,925
Could be just a coincidence.

384
00:16:56,050 --> 00:16:59,393
Or it could be where
this whole thing started.

385
00:16:59,559 --> 00:17:01,664
Our new high-frequency program

386
00:17:01,789 --> 00:17:04,200
employs computerized algorithms
that operate

387
00:17:04,325 --> 00:17:07,985
at a speed unmatched
by traditional trading methods.

388
00:17:08,151 --> 00:17:10,206
Since its implementation,

389
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:13,376
returns here at Martin/Charles
have been up over 30%.

390
00:17:13,501 --> 00:17:14,659
Man:
Wow.

391
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:18,264
Now, as you can see,

392
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:21,167
our one-, three- and five-year
growth projections

393
00:17:21,292 --> 00:17:24,085
in HFT are quite impressive.

394
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:26,055
What about the ten-year projection?

395
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,673
Can you hold that rate of growth?

396
00:17:27,798 --> 00:17:29,108
Oh, I believe that we can.

397
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:30,393
Unfortunately,

398
00:17:30,518 --> 00:17:32,478
our software designer
isn't here with us today,

399
00:17:32,603 --> 00:17:35,179
so I'll have to get back to you
with specific numbers.

400
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:36,782
Malcolm:
Actually, Andrew,

401
00:17:37,055 --> 00:17:38,901
all the data
for those projections is here.

402
00:17:39,026 --> 00:17:41,020
If you'd like,
I can run a quick program,

403
00:17:41,145 --> 00:17:42,478
figure out those numbers for you.

404
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:43,956
Oh. Wonderful.

405
00:17:44,081 --> 00:17:45,064
Thank you, Malcolm.

406
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,960
If you wouldn't
all mind bearing with us.

407
00:17:48,085 --> 00:17:48,995
Man:
Not at all.

408
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:51,445
(Typing)

409
00:17:57,210 --> 00:18:02,206
Well, as you can see,
we can hold that rate of growth.

410
00:18:04,624 --> 00:18:07,086
Bridget: <i>Okay, this should be
the last of it.</i>

411
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:09,231
All right, I know
this seems daunting,

412
00:18:09,356 --> 00:18:12,184
but, uh, most of the auction
items are already labeled.

413
00:18:12,309 --> 00:18:15,094
We just have to come up
with minimum bids

414
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,072
and sort through everything.

415
00:18:16,197 --> 00:18:17,513
Oh, and we got to figure out

416
00:18:17,679 --> 00:18:19,825
a layout for the, uh,
night of the party.

417
00:18:19,950 --> 00:18:22,059
Okay, that sounds like a lot.

418
00:18:22,225 --> 00:18:24,519
I'm happy to help.

419
00:18:26,656 --> 00:18:29,402
I know it must seem weird,
my offering to help.

420
00:18:29,527 --> 00:18:32,421
I... I realize things have been...

421
00:18:32,546 --> 00:18:34,447
Strained between us.

422
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:37,093
To be honest, I was shocked

423
00:18:37,218 --> 00:18:38,928
that you actually followed through.

424
00:18:39,053 --> 00:18:40,680
I thought you were just putting on

425
00:18:40,805 --> 00:18:42,496
a good face for our husbands.

426
00:18:42,662 --> 00:18:46,152
I really want things to
be better between us.

427
00:18:46,277 --> 00:18:49,253
I mean, we were friends once, right?

428
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:51,974
I thought we were.

429
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:53,841
Until that weekend.

430
00:18:56,486 --> 00:18:58,345
You know, maybe if we
talked about it...

431
00:18:58,511 --> 00:18:59,765
You know what?
We did enough talking.

432
00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:01,100
Or at least you did.

433
00:19:01,225 --> 00:19:03,142
You practically threatened me.

434
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:05,144
I never said anything
about what I saw,

435
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:08,160
so I just would like that
to be the end of it.

436
00:19:09,499 --> 00:19:12,478
Greer, I'm not the person
that I used to be, and...

437
00:19:12,603 --> 00:19:16,332
I'm definitely not the
person I was that weekend.

438
00:19:16,457 --> 00:19:19,408
I-I hope you'll give me
the chance to prove it.

439
00:19:19,574 --> 00:19:21,285
(Elevator bell dings,
doors slide open)

440
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:23,329
Juliet:
Hey.

441
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:27,266
Didn't realize you had company.

442
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,145
Juliet, you remember Mrs. Sheridan?

443
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,961
She's in charge
of your school benefit.

444
00:19:31,127 --> 00:19:32,098
Hi, Juliet.

445
00:19:32,223 --> 00:19:33,714
- It's good to see you again.
- Hi.

446
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,634
You know what?
I really should get going.

447
00:19:35,759 --> 00:19:37,551
Are you okay with everything here?

448
00:19:37,717 --> 00:19:39,905
Not a problem.
Great.

449
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:42,775
And, Greer,
I-I would love to revisit this,

450
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:44,944
you know, sometime,
if you're willing to...

451
00:19:45,069 --> 00:19:46,268
(Elevator bell dings)

452
00:19:46,434 --> 00:19:48,114
Hey, so this, uh, thing

453
00:19:48,239 --> 00:19:49,647
you're doing tomorrow night,

454
00:19:49,813 --> 00:19:53,150
you're not going
to make me go, are you?

455
00:19:53,316 --> 00:19:55,487
Well, considering it's 20 feet
from your bedroom,

456
00:19:55,612 --> 00:19:58,072
I was hoping you would at least
put in an appearance.

457
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,992
- What?
- I offered up the apartment.

458
00:20:00,117 --> 00:20:01,909
They wanted an intimate setting.

459
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:03,345
It's not that big a deal.

460
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:05,548
I mean, it's just some
board members and their guests

461
00:20:05,673 --> 00:20:07,748
and a few people from your school.

462
00:20:08,575 --> 00:20:10,084
You mean, like, teachers?

463
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:15,965
Please tell me you
didn't invite Mr. Carpenter.

464
00:20:16,131 --> 00:20:17,341
I thought he was your favorite.

465
00:20:17,507 --> 00:20:18,394
No.

466
00:20:18,519 --> 00:20:20,012
No. There's no way.

467
00:20:20,137 --> 00:20:21,971
I'm not going
to your stupid fund-raiser.

468
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:24,807
Juliet, what's wrong?
Nothing.

469
00:20:27,977 --> 00:20:29,371
It's just...

470
00:20:29,496 --> 00:20:33,649
I have to see my stupid teachers
every day at school,

471
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:37,027
and now I have to deal
with them in my own house?

472
00:20:37,193 --> 00:20:38,497
You were a great help today.

473
00:20:38,622 --> 00:20:41,240
Never seen anyone
write code so quickly.

474
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:43,219
Claudine will give you a call

475
00:20:43,344 --> 00:20:45,494
when she cuts your check.

476
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:48,540
You know, if you ever feel
like changing fields,

477
00:20:48,665 --> 00:20:50,374
give me a call.

478
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,377
We could use someone like you.

479
00:20:52,502 --> 00:20:53,846
Wow.

480
00:20:53,971 --> 00:20:55,462
I'm flattered.

481
00:20:58,548 --> 00:21:00,486
(Distant siren wailing)

482
00:21:00,611 --> 00:21:02,861
(Helicopter passing by)

483
00:21:18,828 --> 00:21:20,529
Ah, thank you, Jessie.

484
00:21:20,695 --> 00:21:22,124
Jessie:
You're welcome, sir.

485
00:21:22,249 --> 00:21:24,408
(Indistinct conversation)

486
00:21:24,574 --> 00:21:25,377
Yes, sir.
Okay, see you later.

487
00:21:25,502 --> 00:21:27,002
Thank you, sir.

488
00:21:31,758 --> 00:21:33,585
Hey, Henry, it's me.

489
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:36,856
I-I might be a few minutes late,
but I'm coming, so...

490
00:21:36,981 --> 00:21:39,598
Wait for me, please.

491
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:42,651
(Bell dings)

492
00:22:01,903 --> 00:22:04,039
♪

493
00:22:31,015 --> 00:22:32,226
(Typing)

494
00:22:35,104 --> 00:22:36,188
(Beeping)

495
00:22:40,877 --> 00:22:41,860
(Beeping)

496
00:22:50,076 --> 00:22:52,170
(Sighs softly)

497
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:15,811
(Elevator bell dings)

498
00:23:15,977 --> 00:23:17,612
(Gasps)

499
00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:39,426
{pub}Andrew Martin.

500
00:23:39,551 --> 00:23:40,878
Olivia.

501
00:23:41,044 --> 00:23:42,379
Yeah.

502
00:23:42,545 --> 00:23:44,006
Hang on.
Y-you're breaking up.

503
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:48,602
Mm-hmm. Go ahead.

504
00:23:48,727 --> 00:23:50,137
Look, could you talk slower?

505
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:53,897
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

506
00:23:55,433 --> 00:23:57,770
Look, we should make sure
we get a better line

507
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:01,106
if you're gonna patch him through.

508
00:24:01,272 --> 00:24:02,166
Mm.

509
00:24:02,291 --> 00:24:03,484
Actually, it's better now, really.

510
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:05,619
John, how are you?

511
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:06,653
Good.

512
00:24:08,996 --> 00:24:11,248
(Panting)

513
00:24:17,071 --> 00:24:20,084
Screw you, Siobhan.

514
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,552
Right.

515
00:24:21,677 --> 00:24:23,462
I'll check when I'm back
in the office.

516
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:25,139
Excellent.
So you're happy?

517
00:24:25,264 --> 00:24:27,174
Wonderful, wonderful.
That's great news.

518
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:28,092
(Elevator bell dings)

519
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:29,510
Okay, thanks.
Talk to you soon.

520
00:24:29,635 --> 00:24:30,477
Bye.

521
00:24:30,602 --> 00:24:32,346
I didn't expect you to be here.

522
00:24:32,512 --> 00:24:33,680
Andrew:
I forgot my briefcase.

523
00:24:33,805 --> 00:24:35,799
Bridget: I'm gonna get
that thing chained to your wrist.

524
00:24:35,924 --> 00:24:36,892
(Andrew chuckles)

525
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:38,468
Did you get a chance
to talk to Juliet?

526
00:24:38,593 --> 00:24:40,737
I did. And she swore
that everything was fine.

527
00:24:40,862 --> 00:24:42,606
Even promised to make an
appearance at the party tonight.

528
00:24:42,731 --> 00:24:43,649
Bridget:
Really?

529
00:24:43,815 --> 00:24:45,818
I guess I overreacted.

530
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:49,446
She was just acting so funny
when I mentioned that teacher.

531
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:51,573
Maybe he gave her a bad grade.

532
00:24:51,739 --> 00:24:53,834
You buy a new dress yet?

533
00:24:53,959 --> 00:24:55,869
Bridget:
I've got it narrowed down to three.

534
00:24:56,035 --> 00:24:59,373
But I can't decide if I want
to go big or understated

535
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:00,757
to show off the amazing ring

536
00:25:00,882 --> 00:25:03,633
that my impossibly handsome
husband gave me.

537
00:25:06,546 --> 00:25:08,048
Andrew:
Doesn't matter what dress you choose,

538
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:10,884
I'll only be thinking about
how I can tear it off.

539
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:13,176
Hmm, I like the way you think.

540
00:25:16,264 --> 00:25:17,691
Bridget:
Oh, you should go to work.

541
00:25:17,816 --> 00:25:19,893
I have a million things I have to do.

542
00:25:20,059 --> 00:25:21,879
To be continued?

543
00:25:22,004 --> 00:25:23,480
Most definitely.

544
00:25:27,575 --> 00:25:28,775
(Elevator bell dings)

545
00:25:48,379 --> 00:25:49,464
(Sighs)

546
00:25:49,631 --> 00:25:51,798
(Shower running)

547
00:26:21,495 --> 00:26:23,747
♪

548
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,656
♪

549
00:27:04,905 --> 00:27:05,782
(Sighs)

550
00:27:05,907 --> 00:27:07,334
(Line ringing)

551
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:09,136
Come on, Henry, pick up.
Pick up.

552
00:27:09,261 --> 00:27:10,420
Henry (Recorded):
Hey, you've reached Henry Butler.

553
00:27:10,545 --> 00:27:11,722
Please leave a message at the tone.

554
00:27:11,847 --> 00:27:13,966
Damn it.

555
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:27,604
(Gasps)

556
00:27:30,481 --> 00:27:32,615
(Phone ringing)

557
00:27:34,869 --> 00:27:36,580
Hello.

558
00:27:36,705 --> 00:27:40,083
The caterers are here already?

559
00:27:40,208 --> 00:27:41,335
Uh, yeah, you can send them up.

560
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:42,828
Could you also do me a favor?

561
00:27:42,994 --> 00:27:45,422
Can you see if you could
find me a plumber?

562
00:27:45,547 --> 00:27:48,091
Thank you.

563
00:27:48,374 --> 00:27:50,510
♪ I didn't know when to expect you ♪

564
00:27:50,635 --> 00:27:51,661
Thank you so much.

565
00:27:51,786 --> 00:27:52,763
I really appreciate it.

566
00:27:52,888 --> 00:27:54,804
Thanks for your support.

567
00:27:56,799 --> 00:28:00,503
♪ And though they all
try to possess you ♪

568
00:28:00,628 --> 00:28:04,691
♪ I'm still the one
you choose to call ♪

569
00:28:04,816 --> 00:28:07,861
♪ I don't know
just where you came from ♪

570
00:28:07,986 --> 00:28:09,479
♪ and I need you now...

571
00:28:12,356 --> 00:28:15,861
You look amazing.

572
00:28:16,027 --> 00:28:17,779
You don't look too shabby yourself.

573
00:28:17,945 --> 00:28:20,324
Where's your ring?

574
00:28:21,982 --> 00:28:23,243
Um, I...

575
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,786
I took it to get resized.

576
00:28:26,662 --> 00:28:29,333
It fell off again today.

577
00:28:29,458 --> 00:28:31,752
Um, I really should have
taken it yesterday.

578
00:28:31,918 --> 00:28:34,638
Well, you'll just have to
show it off at the next party.

579
00:28:34,763 --> 00:28:36,473
Any sign of Juliet?

580
00:28:36,598 --> 00:28:38,091
Not yet.

581
00:28:38,216 --> 00:28:39,676
Hmm.

582
00:28:39,842 --> 00:28:41,803
Can you see him?

583
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:45,640
Mm, he seems kind of bored.

584
00:28:45,806 --> 00:28:48,935
Maybe he'll leave.

585
00:28:51,028 --> 00:28:55,609
I still don't understand why
you won't talk to your parents.

586
00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:58,820
'cause I don't want
to screw things up.

587
00:28:58,986 --> 00:29:01,823
I've done a lot of crappy stuff.

588
00:29:03,574 --> 00:29:06,209
My stepmom used to hate me.

589
00:29:08,496 --> 00:29:11,041
Sometimes I think my dad did, too.

590
00:29:14,084 --> 00:29:17,080
But lately, things are, like,

591
00:29:17,205 --> 00:29:20,300
not awful between us.

592
00:29:20,425 --> 00:29:22,135
It just got normal.

593
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:24,388
And I kind of want
it to stay that way.

594
00:29:27,898 --> 00:29:30,936
Juliet, you're not dressed yet?

595
00:29:31,102 --> 00:29:32,312
Do I have to remind you how hard

596
00:29:32,437 --> 00:29:33,522
Siobhan has worked on this party?

597
00:29:33,688 --> 00:29:35,315
I got it, dad.

598
00:29:35,481 --> 00:29:37,192
Really, I do.

599
00:29:37,358 --> 00:29:41,738
I-I just, I can't get
dressed till you leave.

600
00:29:41,904 --> 00:29:44,741
Well, quick as you can, please.

601
00:29:44,907 --> 00:29:47,066
♪

602
00:29:52,673 --> 00:29:55,085
Quite simple, actually.

603
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:57,539
Okay, I think we've shown enough
school spirit for one night.

604
00:29:57,705 --> 00:29:59,222
So let's congratulate your stepmom

605
00:29:59,347 --> 00:30:01,057
and get the hell out of here.

606
00:30:01,182 --> 00:30:02,467
Now's not a great time.

607
00:30:04,260 --> 00:30:06,138
Woman:
It's such a great party...

608
00:30:14,278 --> 00:30:15,188
What are you...

609
00:30:15,354 --> 00:30:16,690
Don't judge. Support.

610
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:19,159
It's the only way
I'll get through tonight.

611
00:30:19,284 --> 00:30:21,027
(Chuckles)

612
00:30:21,152 --> 00:30:23,697
Okay.

613
00:30:23,863 --> 00:30:24,698
You have to.

614
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:26,283
Hey.

615
00:30:26,449 --> 00:30:27,984
Hey.

616
00:30:28,109 --> 00:30:29,453
I didn't expect to see you.

617
00:30:29,619 --> 00:30:31,087
Really?

618
00:30:31,212 --> 00:30:32,789
Because you couldn't stop calling me.

619
00:30:32,955 --> 00:30:35,992
I didn't call you.

620
00:30:36,117 --> 00:30:37,878
Did someone call you from my number?

621
00:30:38,044 --> 00:30:40,597
No, the number was blocked, but I...

622
00:30:40,722 --> 00:30:42,924
Are you seriously
gonna do this to me again?

623
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:45,093
Wait, doing what to you?

624
00:30:45,259 --> 00:30:46,553
I had a meeting
at <i>the new yorker</i> today,

625
00:30:46,719 --> 00:30:48,180
and I missed it because
of you, Siobhan.

626
00:30:48,346 --> 00:30:49,439
Wait, Henry, calm down...

627
00:30:49,564 --> 00:30:51,441
I'm done.
I am done with you.

628
00:30:51,566 --> 00:30:53,510
I do not want to see you,
I don't want to think about you,

629
00:30:53,635 --> 00:30:54,844
I don't even want
to talk to you again.

630
00:30:54,969 --> 00:30:56,438
You stay out of my life.

631
00:31:10,284 --> 00:31:12,204
Here.

632
00:31:12,370 --> 00:31:13,630
Thank you.

633
00:31:13,755 --> 00:31:15,922
Mm-hmm.

634
00:31:22,930 --> 00:31:24,124
Hey.

635
00:31:24,249 --> 00:31:25,550
You okay?

636
00:31:27,351 --> 00:31:28,678
Yeah, I'm fine.

637
00:31:31,772 --> 00:31:34,601
Henry seemed pretty upset.

638
00:31:36,276 --> 00:31:38,388
Yeah, he's not doing so well.

639
00:31:38,513 --> 00:31:40,148
But you can't really blame him.

640
00:31:40,314 --> 00:31:43,151
You guys still together?

641
00:31:46,203 --> 00:31:50,283
Um, no, I... I ended it.

642
00:31:52,025 --> 00:31:53,453
Did Andrew find out?

643
00:31:53,619 --> 00:31:56,923
No.

644
00:31:57,048 --> 00:31:59,459
Greer, I-I know I have no right
to ask you this, but...

645
00:31:59,625 --> 00:32:01,761
If I didn't say anything
after that weekend,

646
00:32:01,886 --> 00:32:03,263
I'm not going to now.

647
00:32:03,546 --> 00:32:07,601
That weekend
where we stopped speaking was

648
00:32:07,726 --> 00:32:11,596
because you found out
about the affair.

649
00:32:11,762 --> 00:32:13,723
It didn't just
destroy our friendship.

650
00:32:13,848 --> 00:32:16,926
It ruined my relationship with Gemma.

651
00:32:17,051 --> 00:32:20,597
You know, I couldn't look her
in the eye after that.

652
00:32:20,722 --> 00:32:22,190
I hated you for that.

653
00:32:24,274 --> 00:32:26,987
I don't blame you.

654
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:28,738
And I'm sorry.

655
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:32,242
More sorry than I know
how to put into words.

656
00:32:36,303 --> 00:32:37,631
You know, I have to admit,

657
00:32:37,756 --> 00:32:40,125
it's been really great
working with you this week.

658
00:32:40,291 --> 00:32:43,420
I've had a good time, too.

659
00:32:43,586 --> 00:32:46,556
I just have to ask...

660
00:32:46,681 --> 00:32:49,175
The flowers you brought
to dinner the other night...?

661
00:32:49,341 --> 00:32:52,629
I was just being a bitch.

662
00:32:52,754 --> 00:32:55,482
I couldn't believe that
you actually said yes to dinner,

663
00:32:55,607 --> 00:32:57,767
and I wanted to throw you
off your game.

664
00:32:57,933 --> 00:32:59,653
I'm sorry.

665
00:32:59,778 --> 00:33:01,104
It's okay.

666
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:02,972
(Sighs)

667
00:33:03,097 --> 00:33:05,442
Who would've thought flowers
could mean so much?

668
00:33:05,567 --> 00:33:07,027
Yeah, well, I can't

669
00:33:07,193 --> 00:33:09,613
see peonies without
thinking about that weekend.

670
00:33:09,738 --> 00:33:12,082
They were all over
the hotel, remember?

671
00:33:12,207 --> 00:33:13,491
Hotel pivoine.

672
00:33:16,744 --> 00:33:18,455
You know, I go to Boston
all the time,

673
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:21,291
and I don't go anywhere near
that hotel anymore.

674
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:26,452
(Talking, laughing)

675
00:33:28,639 --> 00:33:30,800
You sure she's young enough for you?

676
00:33:30,966 --> 00:33:32,802
'cause...

677
00:33:32,968 --> 00:33:35,021
I know your type.

678
00:33:35,146 --> 00:33:37,346
And she's not it.

679
00:33:40,267 --> 00:33:43,029
Excuse me.

680
00:33:43,154 --> 00:33:45,031
Juliet.

681
00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:46,941
I think, uh, you and I should talk...

682
00:33:47,107 --> 00:33:48,777
Don't touch me!

683
00:33:48,943 --> 00:33:50,236
I got it.

684
00:33:50,402 --> 00:33:52,188
I'm fine.

685
00:33:52,313 --> 00:33:55,033
You, young lady, are drunk.

686
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:56,859
You're boring.

687
00:33:56,984 --> 00:33:58,953
And so are all your stupid friends.

688
00:33:59,119 --> 00:34:01,790
Andrea, it's time for you to go home.

689
00:34:01,956 --> 00:34:03,917
Judith's turning in for the night.

690
00:34:04,083 --> 00:34:06,209
Right now.

691
00:34:07,628 --> 00:34:09,796
(Knocking on door)

692
00:34:11,098 --> 00:34:12,008
Hey.

693
00:34:14,510 --> 00:34:17,764
Your dad told me what happened.

694
00:34:17,930 --> 00:34:21,718
I know I ruined your party.

695
00:34:21,843 --> 00:34:23,520
I get it, I'm a total screw-up.

696
00:34:23,686 --> 00:34:27,065
Juliet, I don't care about the party.

697
00:34:27,231 --> 00:34:29,567
(Sniffles)

698
00:34:29,733 --> 00:34:32,028
You know, I've ruined
my fair share of parties

699
00:34:32,194 --> 00:34:33,446
drinking too much.

700
00:34:33,612 --> 00:34:36,082
True story.

701
00:34:36,207 --> 00:34:38,284
But usually when I did it,
there was a reason.

702
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,830
Juliet, I know something's going on.

703
00:34:41,996 --> 00:34:45,250
Please, try and talk to me.

704
00:34:48,852 --> 00:34:51,097
The other day...

705
00:34:51,222 --> 00:34:53,422
When I mentioned Mr. Carpenter...

706
00:34:59,930 --> 00:35:04,060
Did something happen between you two?

707
00:35:09,648 --> 00:35:11,774
(Talking indistinctly)

708
00:35:13,944 --> 00:35:15,613
Carpenter.

709
00:35:16,822 --> 00:35:18,507
(Grunts)

710
00:35:24,142 --> 00:35:25,373
{pub}What the hell is your problem?

711
00:35:25,539 --> 00:35:27,125
- Get out of my house.
- What's going on?

712
00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:30,253
If you come near my stepdaughter
again, I will kill you!

713
00:35:30,419 --> 00:35:32,589
Juliet, what is she talking about?

714
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,549
Get out, now!

715
00:35:34,715 --> 00:35:36,878
Woman:
What?

716
00:35:37,509 --> 00:35:39,631
(Guests murmuring)

717
00:35:40,721 --> 00:35:43,975
What the hell's going on?

718
00:36:02,622 --> 00:36:04,816
Oh, God.

719
00:36:04,941 --> 00:36:06,498
I don't want to talk about it.

720
00:36:06,664 --> 00:36:08,833
Juliet...

721
00:36:08,999 --> 00:36:10,543
Don't even.

722
00:36:15,084 --> 00:36:18,051
Why did you do that in front
of all those people?

723
00:36:20,302 --> 00:36:23,001
All I wanted

724
00:36:23,126 --> 00:36:24,586
was to forget about what happened,

725
00:36:24,711 --> 00:36:26,476
and now the whole world knows.

726
00:36:26,642 --> 00:36:29,041
I am so sorry.

727
00:36:29,166 --> 00:36:30,192
I wasn't thinking.

728
00:36:30,317 --> 00:36:32,273
I was just so angry
I couldn't see straight.

729
00:36:32,439 --> 00:36:34,603
No kidding.

730
00:36:35,471 --> 00:36:37,070
Just get out.

731
00:36:47,416 --> 00:36:50,012
Daddy, please.

732
00:36:50,137 --> 00:36:51,918
Leave me alone.

733
00:37:23,006 --> 00:37:24,284
{pub}Want some coffee?

734
00:37:24,450 --> 00:37:25,718
Uh, no, actually.

735
00:37:25,843 --> 00:37:28,704
I just wanted to
ask you a couple questions.

736
00:37:28,871 --> 00:37:30,806
Great. I love questions.

737
00:37:30,931 --> 00:37:32,125
Way more than tips.

738
00:37:33,266 --> 00:37:35,844
I'm investigating
this man... John Delario.

739
00:37:35,969 --> 00:37:37,255
He also goes by Charlie Young.

740
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:39,340
I know he was in
the area in September,

741
00:37:39,506 --> 00:37:41,517
but what I need to know
is if anyone saw him with her.

742
00:37:41,642 --> 00:37:43,219
Name's Bridget Kelly.

743
00:37:45,144 --> 00:37:46,605
They were in here, once.

744
00:37:46,730 --> 00:37:48,683
But not in September. May.

745
00:37:48,849 --> 00:37:51,853
That can't be right.
Bridget was in Wyoming in may.

746
00:37:52,019 --> 00:37:54,022
Okay, then.

747
00:37:54,188 --> 00:37:55,280
You sure it was may?

748
00:37:55,564 --> 00:37:57,166
I'm positive.
It was on my birthday.

749
00:37:57,291 --> 00:37:59,618
I was trying to get out early,
but she was a bitch.

750
00:37:59,743 --> 00:38:02,405
Waved me down every two seconds,
and then stiffed me on the tip.

751
00:38:03,429 --> 00:38:04,390
Remember anything else?

752
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:05,657
What they talked about, maybe?

753
00:38:05,782 --> 00:38:08,260
The guy said her name once,
and she shut him down quick.

754
00:38:08,385 --> 00:38:09,787
He called her something weird.

755
00:38:09,953 --> 00:38:12,070
I never heard it before.

756
00:38:13,272 --> 00:38:14,292
He call her Siobhan?

757
00:38:14,458 --> 00:38:15,734
That's it.

758
00:38:15,859 --> 00:38:17,102
What kind of a name is that?

759
00:38:17,227 --> 00:38:18,796
Man:
Excuse me, miss?

760
00:38:22,466 --> 00:38:24,827
John Delario...

761
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:29,098
What the hell were you doing
with Siobhan Martin?

762
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:33,892
(Typing)

763
00:38:56,299 --> 00:38:58,086
How'd it go at the police station?

764
00:38:58,252 --> 00:39:00,813
Can I talk about it later?

765
00:39:00,938 --> 00:39:03,298
I need to speak with Juliet.

766
00:39:03,423 --> 00:39:05,510
She's still in her room.

767
00:39:05,676 --> 00:39:07,776
She won't come out.

768
00:39:08,811 --> 00:39:11,973
But I was able to slip her
a tray of food, so...

769
00:39:12,098 --> 00:39:13,726
That was a start.

770
00:39:16,228 --> 00:39:17,913
Andrew...

771
00:39:18,038 --> 00:39:21,734
I'm really sorry about
decking Carpenter.

772
00:39:21,900 --> 00:39:23,368
I just...

773
00:39:23,652 --> 00:39:26,030
Felt this need to protect Juliet.

774
00:39:26,196 --> 00:39:28,296
Like a mother would.

775
00:39:28,965 --> 00:39:31,993
I'm not angry at you, Siobhan.

776
00:39:32,118 --> 00:39:34,163
I'm the one who failed her.

777
00:39:34,288 --> 00:39:35,665
I should've seen what was going on.

778
00:39:35,831 --> 00:39:38,183
Wait, no, she did
everything she could

779
00:39:38,308 --> 00:39:39,752
to keep you from finding out.

780
00:39:39,918 --> 00:39:41,002
But you knew.

781
00:39:41,127 --> 00:39:42,296
And you tried to tell me.

782
00:39:42,462 --> 00:39:44,506
I knew that something was off,

783
00:39:44,631 --> 00:39:45,941
that was it.

784
00:39:46,066 --> 00:39:47,342
It didn't stop me
from telling everyone

785
00:39:47,467 --> 00:39:49,303
how great she was doing
at her new school.

786
00:39:49,469 --> 00:39:53,071
We can't sit here
and beat ourselves up.

787
00:39:53,348 --> 00:39:55,484
I've done too much of that
in my life,

788
00:39:55,609 --> 00:39:56,685
it doesn't get you anywhere.

789
00:39:56,810 --> 00:39:59,856
♪ Eyes going blind
we'll get through this.

790
00:40:00,022 --> 00:40:02,191
As a family.

791
00:40:02,357 --> 00:40:04,485
I promise.

792
00:40:06,535 --> 00:40:10,732
♪ Soul is lost

793
00:40:10,857 --> 00:40:14,412
♪ my body makes me lose

794
00:40:16,872 --> 00:40:18,458
♪ it all what are you doing here?

795
00:40:18,624 --> 00:40:20,709
Annafried let me in.

796
00:40:20,834 --> 00:40:22,837
She took the boys out for dessert.

797
00:40:23,003 --> 00:40:24,630
Yeah, I know that.

798
00:40:24,796 --> 00:40:27,889
I know you're angry at me.

799
00:40:29,075 --> 00:40:31,019
I've been acting like
a different person,

800
00:40:31,144 --> 00:40:32,263
and it doesn't make sense.

801
00:40:32,429 --> 00:40:34,390
Get out.

802
00:40:34,556 --> 00:40:35,924
No.

803
00:40:36,049 --> 00:40:38,978
Please, hear me out.

804
00:40:39,144 --> 00:40:43,665
I'm sorry for yesterday.

805
00:40:43,790 --> 00:40:49,037
And the day before,
and the last few months.

806
00:40:49,162 --> 00:40:50,490
And Gemma.

807
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:56,011
Henry, if I could change any
of it, take it back, I would.

808
00:40:56,136 --> 00:40:59,707
♪ Eyes go blind...
I miss you so much.

809
00:40:59,873 --> 00:41:01,016
That's funny.

810
00:41:01,141 --> 00:41:04,295
Because yesterday you wanted
nothing to do with me.

811
00:41:04,461 --> 00:41:07,756
It wasn't supposed to be like this.

812
00:41:07,881 --> 00:41:09,558
But I'm going to fix it, I promise.

813
00:41:09,683 --> 00:41:11,894
Fix what, Siobhan?

814
00:41:12,019 --> 00:41:13,028
You are in charge.

815
00:41:13,153 --> 00:41:14,529
You want me? Here I am.

816
00:41:14,654 --> 00:41:16,598
You want to just live happily
ever after with Andrew,

817
00:41:16,723 --> 00:41:18,017
walk away.

818
00:41:18,183 --> 00:41:19,651
I can't!

819
00:41:19,776 --> 00:41:21,813
Henry, I love you.

820
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:23,538
All right, fine. Fine.

821
00:41:23,663 --> 00:41:25,290
Let's say that that's the truth.

822
00:41:25,415 --> 00:41:28,877
All right?
That you really love me.

823
00:41:29,002 --> 00:41:30,779
Then I want to know one thing:

824
00:41:30,904 --> 00:41:32,948
Who was the person
at the party yesterday?

825
00:41:33,073 --> 00:41:34,325
Because it's not the same person

826
00:41:34,491 --> 00:41:37,386
who's standing here
in front of me right now.

827
00:41:37,511 --> 00:41:39,080
Tell me.

828
00:41:39,246 --> 00:41:41,624
Who the hell are you?

